      "title": "Add features",
      "description": "### Add Features\r\n\r\nOk, great. Now that our application can succesfully read and display the contents of the CSV file, let's now ask Copilot to add a feature.\r\n\r\nWe want to display a chart that visualizes the aggregated suggestion versus acceptance by day. \r\n\r\nIn this scenario, we need to be very clear and concise on what we need Copilot to suggest for us. Let's try this out:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n```text\r\nI want to add a line chart that visualises the suggestions versus acceptance counts by day\r\n```\r\n&nbsp;\r\nBefore asking Copilot Chat, remember that the analysedata.py file is open. We expect that Copilot will use this as context for its suggestion. \r\n\r\nOk, let's see what Copilot gives us with this prompt.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n(Make the analysedata.py the active tab, then switch to Copilot chat)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLet's review the code then copy it over into our analysedata.py.\r\n\r\n(Switch to analysedata.py, while having Chat opened as well)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSelect all text from analysedata.py, then overwrite it with the code from Copilot Chat.\r\nRe-run the application after copying the code. Streamlit provides a built-in re-run that executes the file from the beginning when you make any changes to it.\r\n\r\nPress `Next` to Continue"
