      "title": "Date format error",
      "description": "### Asking help about errors\r\n\r\nIn case there are more errors that occur, simply copying and pasting the error message in the chat window will allow Copilot to assist you in identifying and suggesting potential solutions.\r\n\r\nTake note though of this term called the `Context Window` in every Large Language Models, including OpenAI. This is the limit that Copilot chat can handle. \r\n\r\nAs of this writing, 4096 tokens is the context window, or around 4,000+ words. This is enough to write a short story, but remember the three S's in our prompt crafting session? Simple, Short and Specific.\r\n\r\nSo be cautious of copying large amounts of error logs into Copilot chat as it may hallucinate or provide inaccurate suggestions due to the large amount of context you provide it.\r\n\r\nUse your best judgement and only provide the relevant error stack that you need Copilot chat help with.\r\n\r\n"
